    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          A plumber charges <m>\dollar50</m> for a service call plus <m>\dollar80</m> per hour.
          If she spends no longer than 8 hours a day at any one site,
          find a linear function that represents her total daily charges <m>C</m>
          (in dollars)
          as a function of time <m>t</m>
          (in hours)
          spent at any one given location.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>C(t) = 80t + 50</m>, <m>0 \leq t \leq 8</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
