    <p>
      In the following exercises,
      compute the average rate of change of the function over the specified interval.
    </p>
    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          <m>f(x) = x^{3}, \; [-1, 2]</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>\dfrac{2^{3} - (-1)^{3}}{2 - (-1)} = 3</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>
    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          <m>f(x) = \dfrac{1}{x}, \; [1, 5]</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>\dfrac{\frac{1}{5} - \frac{1}{1}}{5 - 1} = -\dfrac{1}{5}</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>
    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          <m>f(x) = \sqrt{x}, \; [0, 16]</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>\dfrac{\sqrt{16} - \sqrt{0}}{16 - 0} = \dfrac{1}{4}</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>
    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          <m>f(x) = x^{2}, \; [-3, 3]</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>\dfrac{3^{2} - (-3)^{2}}{3 - (-3)} = 0</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>
    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          <m>f(x) = \dfrac{x + 4}{x - 3}, \; [5, 7]</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>\dfrac{\frac{7 + 4}{7 - 3} - \frac{5 + 4}{5 - 3}}{7 - 5} = -\dfrac{7}{8}</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>
    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          <m>f(x) = 3x^{2} + 2x - 7, \; [-4, 2]</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>\dfrac{(3(2)^{2}+2(2)-7)-(3(-4)^{2}+2(-4)-7)}{2-(-4)}=-4</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>
    <p>
      In the following exercises,
      compute the average rate of change of the given function over the interval <m>[x, x + h]</m>.
      Here we assume <m>[x, x + h]</m> is in the domain of the function.
    </p>
    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          <m>f(x) = x^{3}</m>
        </p>
